						<div class="postbody">I have two problems.<br /><br />One: the programs I've written have horrible problems with button bounce, much bigger than anything I've written on the NES. Am I doing something wrong, or is this a known flaw?<br /><br />Two: In trying to diagnose the above button bounce, I wrote a simple program <span style="font-size: 50%; line-height: normal">(It's a simplified subset of tepples's spadtest, which <em>does</em> work on my hardware)</span> that draws a series of lines (one pixel per button per vsync) corresponding to the buttons that are pressed. It works correctly in every emulator I've tried (including bsnes-plus but not higan), but not on hardware (always returning no-buttons-pressed). What could I be doing wrong?</div>

