			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">From anomie's docs:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;When enabled, the SNES will read 16 bits from each of the 4 controller port<br />&nbsp;data lines into registers $4218-f. This begins between H=32.5 and H=95.5 of<br />&nbsp;the first V-Blank scanline, and ends 4224 master cycles later. Register $4212<br />&nbsp;bit 0 is set during this time.</div><br />So waiting for &quot;begin of vblank&quot;, does somehow ensure that your code will collide with autoread.<br />Even if you've tested the joypad busy bit to be cleared - it will be set shortly thereafter.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

